> that's not a devfs issue. Linux currently doesn't any mechanism for
> attaching labels to volumes, which imo would be the cleanest way.  what
Thud. thud. thud.
Linux filesystems have label strings, even the DOS fs's have serial numbers
And note: per file system (ie partition) not per disk. Per disk labelling
is useless in the longer run because you may restore a single partition of
stuff to a different disk
